content:
Few of the SearchParameter's Canonical URL are not resolving. Attached is the example:
image.png
It's weird coz not all of them complains. For example CodeSystem's code and system search parameters are okay; however date, description, name, status, and url complains (as shown in the image).
@Grahame Grieve any insights on this?
you're probably using the wrong canonical URL

We really need a way to be able to see the canonical URL for search parameters by looking at the spec. Right now, the only way to tell that something is a magic 'shared' search parameter is to download the spec and look at the XML or JSON, which isn't super friendly. Is this already on your list @Grahame Grieve or do you want a Git issue?
but it's a jira task, not a git issue
